Former President Jacob Zuma has dismissed corruption claims against him as propaganda. JOHANNESBURG - Former President Jacob Zuma has dismissed corruption claims against him as propaganda. Zuma was on the campaign trail in eThekwini alongside ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule. READ: SA is relieved Zuma out of office: Tony Leon He says as an ANC member he has every right to campaign for the party. Zuma denied he is plotting to dethrone President Cyril Ramaphosa. READ: Duduzane Zuma introduced me to Gupta brother: Booysen "I’m an ANC member, people should know the processes of the ANC," said Zuma. "What have I done?" he asked. "I'd listen to them if they were to say this is what Zuma has done, that word has been used for propaganda purposes."